
[1]cohere

   COHERE, v.i.

   1. To stick together; to cleave; to be united; to hold fast, as parts
   of the same mass, or as two substances that attract each other. Thus,
   particles of clay cohere; polished surfaces of bodies cohere.

   2. To be well connected; to follow regularly in the natural order; to
   be suited in connection; as the parts of a discourse, or as arguments
   in a train of reasoning.

   3. To suit; to be fitted; to agree.
